        "synopsis": {
            "value": "Sun Tae-Hyeong (Bae In-Hyuk) works as an assistant photographer. He cherishes his freedom and space. Although he looks like a free spirted person, he carries hidden pain within his mind. Woo Hyun-Jin (Roh Jeong-Eui) is a job seeker, who dreams of having an ordinary daily life. Sun Tae-Hyeong and Woo Hyun-Jin are related as in-laws. They don't along with each other and bicker over everything. One day, Sun Tae-Hyeong's older brother and Woo Hyun-Jin's older sister die in an accident, leaving behind their 20 month old baby. Sun Tae-Hyeong and Woo Hyun-Jin begin to live together to raise their nephew together. They face difficult parenting situations and work together to resolve those problems. They also resolve misunderstandings between them and their relationship changes.",
            "source": "asianwiki",
